<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-609-506  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 609 506.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  June 25 1990 n596 p60(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EDA will move toward system design by the year 2000. (electronicdesign automation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rappaport, Andrew S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The future of electronic design engineering is surveyed.andP;  Amongthe trends predicted are greatly increased chip and systemcomplexity, higher silicon operating margins, and smaller boarddesign margins.andP;  Tools will appear that help designers explore andoptimize hardware architectures.andP;  The most important breakthroughwill come near the end of the 1990s, when tools appear thatoperate above the hardware-software partition.andP;  These tools willlead to the replacement of hardware designers and programmers bysystem engineers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Future of ComputingDesignAutomationElectronicsEngineering.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   The closing gap between talent and power. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>